com.kamomileware.maven.plugin.opencms

Class ModuleMojo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.maven.plugin.AbstractMojo
      • com.kamomileware.maven.plugin.opencms.AbstractModuleMojo
        • com.kamomileware.maven.plugin.opencms.ModuleMojo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.maven.plugin.ContextEnabled, org.apache.maven.plugin.Mojo

    @Mojo(name="module",
      defaultPhase=PACKAGE,
      requiresDependencyResolution=COMPILE_PLUS_RUNTIME)
public class ModuleMojo
extends AbstractModuleMojo
    Build opencms module. The process includes the manifest generation if ${generate.manifest} and module properties descriptor are set. This goal is binded to package building phase for the opencms-module projects.
    Author:
    jagarcia

      • buildModule

        public void buildModule(org.apache.maven.project.MavenProject project,
                        File moduleDirectory)
                 throws org.apache.maven.plugin.MojoExecutionException,
                        org.apache.maven.plugin.MojoFailureException,
                        IOException
        Builds the module for the specified project with the new packaging task thingy Classes, libraries and tld files are copied to the webappDirectory during this phase.
        Parameters:
        project - the maven project
        moduleDirectory - the target directory
        Throws:
        org.apache.maven.plugin.MojoExecutionException - if an error occurred while packaging the webapp
        org.apache.maven.plugin.MojoFailureException - if an unexpected error occurred while packaging the webapp
        IOException - if an error occurred while copying the files
